End Users can download INSTALLER.sh (from the scripts directory) individually.
The installer will alter your .bashrc file.

Developers:
After cloning the repository (or before you start work)
run:
		source ./scripts/work_here.sh
from the top level of the repository.
This is the least destructive method of getting the working directory
ready for development/testing.


#############################################################################
#############################################################################
Developers using Mercurial:

After making the configuration changes below, please use
hg pushall and hg pullall instead of hg push and hg pull

Please add the following entries to your .hg/hgrc file:
# you need to change the USERNAME in the paths Github and SF-Git to your
# username on Github and SourceForge

[extensions]
hgext.bookmarks =
hggit =

[paths]
Github = git+ssh://git@github.com:USERNAME/clonedCodeChecker.git
SF-Git = git+ssh://USERNAME@git.code.sf.net/p/clonedcodechecker/git

[alias]
pushall = !hg bookmark -r default master && hg push Github && hg push SF-Git && hg push
pullall = !hg pull Github && hg pull SF-Git && hg pull

#############################################################################
#############################################################################
Developers using Git:

After making the configuration changes below, please use
git fetchall and git pushall instead of git fetch and git push

Please add the following entries to your .git/config file:
# you need to change the USERNAME in the url and pushurl to your username
# on Github and SourceForge

[remote "origin"]
	url = git@github.com:USERNAME/clonedCodeChecker.git
	fetch = +refs/heads/*:refs/remotes/origin/*
	pushurl = git@github.com:USERNAME/clonedCodeChecker.git
[remote "SF"]
	url = ssh://USERNAME@git.code.sf.net/p/clonedcodechecker/git
	fetch = +refs/heads/*:refs/remotes/SF/*
	pushurl = ssh://USERNAME@git.code.sf.net/p/clonedcodechecker/git
[branch "master"]
	remote = origin
	merge = refs/heads/master
[alias]
	fetchall = !git fetch origin master && git fetch SF master
	pushall = !git push origin master && git push SF master

#############################################################################
#############################################################################
